# Agents run local commands (scaffold)

When local setup or verification is needed (`npm run dev`, `npm run db:migrate:local`, builds, curls against localhost, etc.), **run it yourself** in the terminal. Do **not** end with “run this locally” or paste commands for the user to execute unless they explicitly asked for copy-paste instructions only.

## Do

- Start long-lived dev servers in the **background** when needed; use `curl` or project verify scripts to confirm behavior.
- Report what you ran and what you observed (status codes, key fields, UI behavior).
- Stop or note port conflicts if a server is already running on the expected port.

## Do not

- Delegate routine local verification to the user when you have shell access.
- Block on the user running migrations or `npm run dev` before continuing work you can finish yourself.
